    <div class="post clearfix post-130 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-travel" id="post-130">
    
        <h2 class="title"><a href="http://www.baijinguojiyulecheng.org/montenegro-pulse-launches-new-website/" title="Permalink to Montenegro Pulse Launches New Website" rel="bookmark">Montenegro Pulse Launches New Website</a></h2>
        
        <div class="postmeta-primary">

            <span class="meta_date">August 12, 2016</span>
           &nbsp;  <span class="meta_categories"><a href="http://www.baijinguojiyulecheng.org/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span>

                 
        </div>
        
        <div class="entry clearfix">
            
                        
            <p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</p>
<p>(Bijela, Montenegro)&mdash; Montenegro Pulse has recently announced the launch of their brand new website. The site has been created to be the ultimate destination guide for those who are planning trips to Montenegro and want honest and impartial local advice on the best of Montenegro. At the Montenegro Pulse website, visitors and readers will find information about the top tours, restaurants, attractions, and fun activities that the country has to offer as well as recommendations on the best Montenegro hotels for families and individuals to book.</p>
<p>Sarah Pavlovic, a spokesperson for Montenegro Pulse, commented &ldquo;We are so excited about the launch of our new website. Having come to Montenegro from New Zealand in 2008 on a bit of a whim, we are proud to call this place our home and absolutely love the sunnier climate and the more leisurely pace of life we enjoy here. Montenegro has so much to offer, and yet it remains one of the undiscovered gems of the world. We created this destination guide so that people visiting our beautiful country would have access to insider information that will allow them to not only book the best hotel accommodations, but also know where to find the best and most fun Montenegro attractions.&rdquo;</p>
<p>For those who plan to visit Montenegro, they&rsquo;ll find a plethora of information at Montenegro Pulse about where to eat and drink and what to do once they arrive at their vacation destination. Right from the homepage, readers can explore top destinations like Kotor and Budva, see what it&rsquo;s like to go to top attractions like The Blue Cave and Our Lady of the Rocks, find out where all the best beaches are, get the&nbsp;scoop on top-rated activities like boat tours, whitewater rafting, and wine tasting, and take advantage of in-depth reviews of the Montenegro Pulse team&rsquo;s favorite restaurants across the country.</p>
<p>As Pavlovic goes on to say, &ldquo;Montenegro Pulse is the only site written by native English speakers with years of experience helping people book vacations in Montenegro. We love this beautiful country of ours, and we are confident that vacationers will love it to. It is our hope that this website will help people discover what they need to know to have the trip of a lifetime.&rdquo;</p>
<p>About Montenegro Pulse:</p>
<p>As residents living in the area, the team at Montenegro Pulse knows all of the best places to visit and want to share the best that this country has to offer with visitors from around the world. As a guide to the best things to do and places to stay in Montenegro, the website includes a plethora of helpful tips and secrets that only locals know. Montenegro Pulse&rsquo;s readers and visitors are sure to find useful information and some things to put on their &lsquo;must-do&rsquo; list.</p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://www.wdrb.com/story/32698965/news">http://www.wdrb.com/story/32698965/news</a></p>

        </div>
        
